author: wtopstaff
title: Northern Colorado rolls over UC Davis 56-27
text:
By The Associated Press October 17, 2015 7:46 pm 
GREELEY, Colo. (AP) — Jacob Knipp ran for three scores and threw for a fourth as Northern Colorado rolled over UC Davis 56-27 on Saturday. 
Knipp finished with 186 yards passing and 43 yards rushing for the Bears (4-2, 2-2 Big Sky). Brandon Cartagena had 112 yards rushing, ran for two touchdowns and caught a pass from Knipp for another. 
Knipp and Cartagena teamed up for six touchdowns before the break, including Cartagena’s 57-yard TD run and 34-yard scoring reception in the first quarter, to lead Northern Colorado to a 42-3 lead at halftime. 
Hakeem Deggs scored on a 75-yard run midway through the third quarter and Darius Graham ran it in from a yard out later in the third to seal the win. 
Ben Scott threw for 154 yards for the Aggies (1-6, 1-3). Topics:
